<p class="p">We investigated the influence of individual taxonomic groups on any functional shifts by analysing the relationship between shifts in abundance and trait values. Trends in relative abundance for each taxon were calculated following the same procedure applied above to analyse CWM changes, that is by calculating the bootstrapped mean of linear trends and applying LMM, but here using the relative abundance of each genus as a response variable instead of CWM. The bootstrap means were calculated from a modified version of Equation 
 <xref rid="gcb14413-disp-0003" ref-type="disp-formula" class="xref">(3)</xref> applied to every plot: 
 <disp-formula id="gcb14413-disp-0004" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">(4)</label>
  <math id="nlm-math-4" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mtext class="mtext">RA</mtext>
     <mi class="mi">j</mi>
    </msub>
    <mspace width="0.277778em" class="mspace"/>
    <mo class="mo">∼</mo>
    <mspace width="0.277778em" class="mspace"/>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">β</mi>
     <mn class="mn">1</mn>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">+</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">β</mi>
     <mn class="mn">2</mn>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">×</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mtext class="mtext">time</mtext>
     <mi class="mi">j</mi>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">+</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">ε</mi>
     <mi class="mi">j</mi>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">.</mo>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>where RA is the relative abundance of a genus at plot 
 <italic class="italic">i</italic> and census 
 <italic class="italic">j</italic>. We then use the LMM approach by modifying Equation 
 <xref rid="gcb14413-disp-0004" ref-type="disp-formula" class="xref">(4)</xref> to: 
 <disp-formula id="gcb14413-disp-0005" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">(5)</label>
  <math id="nlm-math-5" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mtext class="mtext">RA</mtext>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">ij</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mspace width="0.277778em" class="mspace"/>
    <mo class="mo">∼</mo>
    <mspace width="0.277778em" class="mspace"/>
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">β</mi>
      <mn class="mn">1</mn>
     </msub>
     <mo class="mo">+</mo>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">a</mi>
      <mi class="mi">i</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mo class="mo">+</mo>
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">β</mi>
      <mn class="mn">2</mn>
     </msub>
     <mo class="mo">+</mo>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">b</mi>
      <mi class="mi">i</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mo class="mo">×</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mtext class="mtext">time</mtext>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">ij</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">+</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">ε</mi>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">ij</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">.</mo>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>
</p>
